---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Dexter Brylle | Site Reliability Engineer | Cloud & DevOps Expert" description="Site Reliability Engineer with 13+ years of experience in observability, cloud infrastructure, and building reliable systems.">
  <section class="page-heading" aria-labelledby="about-title">
    <p class="kicker">Profile</p>
    <h1 id="about-title">About Me</h1>
  </section>

  <section class="prose" aria-labelledby="summary-title">
    <h2 id="summary-title">Summary</h2>
    <p>
      I'm a Site Reliability Engineer and Technical Lead with over 13 years of experience
      bridging software development and enterprise-scale infrastructure. I specialize in
      Observability-as-Code and AI-driven reliability, with a proven track record of
      reducing production incidents by 95% and automating complex CI/CD pipelines.
    </p>
    <p>
      My work spans multi-cloud environments (GCP, Azure, AWS), container orchestration,
      and application security&mdash;with a foundation in microservices architecture and
      full-stack development.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="prose" aria-labelledby="experience-title">
    <h2 id="experience-title">Career</h2>
    <p>
      Currently a Site Reliability Engineer in the banking and financial sector, managing
      enterprise-wide observability through Dynatrace Monaco and designing internal platforms
      for intelligent release verification powered by AI. I design, provision, and maintain
      multi-cloud infrastructure using Terraform across GCP, Azure, and AWS, and serve as
      the security liaison owning vulnerability assessments and compliance documentation for
      production releases.
    </p>
    <p>
      Previously, I led technical teams as a Technical Lead and Senior Backend Engineer,
      managing cloud infrastructure for consumer fitness applications. There I drove down
      production incidents by 95%, transitioned deployments to Blue-Green strategies to
      eliminate downtime, and ran SAST/DAST security scanning programs. My earlier roles
      included directing architecture transformations, building full-stack applications,
      and developing internal tools and automation across startups and global enterprises.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="prose" aria-labelledby="skills-title">
    <h2 id="skills-title">Skills</h2>
    <div class="skills-grid">
      <div class="skill-category">
        <h4>Cloud & Orchestration</h4>
        <p>GCP, Azure, AWS, Kubernetes (GKE/AKS), Docker</p>
      </div>
      <div class="skill-category">
        <h4>Observability & Monitoring</h4>
        <p>Dynatrace (Monaco, DQL, Davis AI), New Relic, Grafana, Prometheus, Datadog</p>
      </div>
      <div class="skill-category">
        <h4>DevOps & Automation</h4>
        <p>GitHub Actions, Terraform, Bitbucket Pipelines, Jenkins, CI/CD</p>
      </div>
      <div class="skill-category">
        <h4>Languages & AI</h4>
        <p>TypeScript/Node.js, Python, Go, Vertex AI, Google Agent Development Kit</p>
      </div>
      <div class="skill-category">
        <h4>Security</h4>
        <p>Snyk, SonarQube, Burp Suite, HashiCorp Vault, SAST/DAST, Threat Modeling</p>
      </div>
      <div class="skill-category">
        <h4>Operating Systems</h4>
        <p>Linux (Ubuntu, Debian), Windows, macOS</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="prose" aria-labelledby="contact-title">
    <h2 id="contact-title">Get In Touch</h2>
    <p>
      Open to opportunities in site reliability engineering, cloud infrastructure, and security architecture.
      Let's talk about how I can help build and maintain your next system.
    </p>
    <div class="link-row">
      <a href="mailto:dexterbrylle@gmail.com">Email Me</a>
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/dexterbrylle/" rel="noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/dexterbrylle" rel="noreferrer">GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .skills-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .skill-category h4 {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .skill-category p {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .skills-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>
